The paper proposes a robust dynamic walking controller using reinforcement learning and a novel whole-body locomotion controller. The focus is on robotics and control, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of reinforcement learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with system dynamics and control, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses 3D physics-based simulation, which could suggest that it belongs to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
